SCORING RUBRIC:

1. contact_and_summary (max 10)
   - Full name, professional email, phone number present            (3 pts)
   - LinkedIn / GitHub / portfolio URL present                      (2 pts)
   - Clear, concise professional summary / objective                (3 pts)
   - Location or work-authorisation note (optional but helpful)     (2 pts)

2. work_experience (max 25)
   - Relevant work experience exists                                (5 pts)
   - Uses strong action verbs (Led, Built, Reduced, Increased...)   (5 pts)
   - At least 2 quantified achievements (%, $, numbers)             (5 pts)
   - Logical career progression / seniority growth                  (5 pts)
   - Descriptions are concise (1-3 bullets per role)                (5 pts)

3. education (max 15)
   - Degree, institution, and graduation year all present           (5 pts)
   - Field of study is relevant to target role                      (5 pts)
   - Relevant coursework, honours, or GPA listed (where useful)     (5 pts)

4. skills (max 15)
   - Technical skills / tools clearly listed                        (5 pts)
   - Soft skills or interpersonal competencies mentioned            (5 pts)
   - Certifications or professional development courses listed      (5 pts)

5. projects (max 20)
   - At least one project described with outcome / impact           (7 pts)
   - Tech stack or methodologies mentioned                          (7 pts)
   - Links to live project / GitHub / portfolio provided            (6 pts)

6. formatting_readability (max 15)
   - Single-page or well-structured multi-page layout               (3 pts)
   - Consistent font, spacing, and section headers                  (3 pts)
   - No spelling or grammar errors visible                          (3 pts)
   - ATS-friendly: no tables, graphics, or multi-column layouts     (3 pts)
   - File is named professionally                                   (3 pts)

BONUS POINTS (up to +5):
   - Unique personal branding or portfolio link with strong content
   - Open-source contributions or publications
   - Multilingual proficiency listed

DEDUCTIONS (up to -5):
   - Spelling / grammar errors clearly present                      (-2)
   - Unprofessional email address                                   (-1)
   - Excessive personal details                                     (-1)
   - Resume exceeds 2 pages for under 5 years experience            (-1)
